Parallel Finite Difference Time Domain (FDTD)

Description:
  This benchmark implements a single-GPU 3D FDTD simulation in OpenCL. It is provided as a library. Check out `test.f90' and `Makefile' to learn how to use the library and compile your program. The kernels `kernels.bin' are provided in binary format. To run your program, an input file `grid.inp' should be provided. Check out the sample file to learn about the input format.

For questions, please contact Zhongliang Chen at zhonchen@ece.neu.edu.

